      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 20/6/74. ¶ T. Ware Esqr &amp;c &amp;c ¶ Acting Under Secretary ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.06.20<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Ware</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">E74/7989, unit 258, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M had been given permission to send G. Luehmann to collect for this purpose<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to J. Francis, 13 March 1874)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but the sets<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also included specimens obtained<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>others.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The contributors of specimens were acknowledged on the label of the specimens;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see images in State Library of Victoria blog 'Baron Ferdinand von Mueller’s Educational Collections of Australian Plants, for example<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <ref target="https://blogs.slv.vic.gov.au/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/clematis-scaled.jpg">
                        <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #0000FF; ">https://blogs.slv.vic.gov.au/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/clematis-scaled.j</seg>
                        <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #0000FF; ">p</seg>
                        <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #0000FF; ">g</seg>
                     </ref>.<space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>For the 'educational collection',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see Maroske (2007)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Lucas et al. (2006), pp. 34-6.</p>
               </note>Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">20/6/74.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. Ware Esqr &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Acting Under Secretary</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor of transmitting herewith a proof-copy of the first fascicle of the educational collections to be submitted to the hon.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Chief Secretary. The number of copies, which amidst the multifarious engagements of the Department and with hardly any means left for its working, I have been able to get ready during the season has been one hundred. As these collections as means of instruction should be accessible to the general community, I beg to suggest, that one copy should be sent to every Mechanic<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Institute, these places being frequented at the hours,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>when artisan's &amp;c have best time for their reading and instruction.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have also the honor to suggest, that the transmission may be effected by circular letter of your office, and in such event I will place the required copies, which will soon be ready, into the General Post Office.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[...]: 'Circulars &amp;c to certain Mechs Insts &amp; P. Libraries 15 &amp; 16.9.74 - H 1333.4.5'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[...]: 'Letter Govt Botanist 21.9.74 - H 1387'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ware: 'Specimen with Mr Greenwood. It is carefully got up but if not carefully handled the collection would soon fall to pieces. | TWW'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Francis: 'Prepare List | It would be objectionable if not impracticable to send these cumbrous packages by post but when completed they can be sent here &amp; I can arrange delivery through the various Members of Parliament. | [J. G. F.] | 26/6/74'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Ware]: 'List of Mechanics Institutions &amp;c herewith | 3/7'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[...]: 'A book of fascicles has been sent to each of the Institutions indicated by a cross. Still there are 19 books remaining. 17.9.74'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">This minute<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">may be</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by M</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">[see T. Ware to M, 21 September 1874]</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">, although its likely to have been siomeine in the CS' department offices</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[...]: 'Part III now ready | Will it be necessary to forwd by circulars? | As to mode of transmissn see minute by Mr Francis of 26.6.74 | (50 Institutes will probably ask to be supplied) | [<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">H. M. L.]</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>| 6-9-76'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">I spent a little time<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="color: #C00000; background-color: #FFFF00; ">on th</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="color: #C00000; background-color: #FFFF00; ">i</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="color: #C00000; background-color: #FFFF00; ">s,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but can't make any suggestions of who it might have been, nor his initials</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For the distribution list, see M to T. Ware, 22 September 1874. For the text of Ware’s circular, see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Williamstown chronicle</seg>, 26 September 1874, p. 3:</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.4722in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">I have the honor to transmit for deposit in your Library a copy of the first Fascicle of an Educational Collection of Botanical Specimens, prepared by the Government Botanist, with a view to supplying means of instruction in the first principles of Botany for all persons in this community who are desirous of entering upon the study of that useful branch of science.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.0277in; text-indent: -0.0277in; color: #C00000; "
                        xml:lang="en">I am not convinced that the sense of the circulars is clear. One or two, one asking about whether the institution wanted one, one covering the transmission? I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have not spent a lot of time on this, though.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sara's long analysis of this<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>says it was not clear how the instutions were selected, which still leaves open the possibility of an initial circular, though whether we should speculate on this is doubtful.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.0277in; text-indent: -0.0277in; color: #C00000; "
                        xml:lang="en">I am also not sure whether all of the minutes cited are<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the original letter, or as seems to be implied, on other letters in the file. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In other words it is a bit of a mess to work out! <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>But I suspect the file is a bit of a mess too!</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The means of the Department are not such, that any exterior<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>elegance could be employed in the preparation, and I may add that the collecting was effected largely on Sundays &amp; Holidays and the other work much in late evening hours. The greater or lesser celerity of the issue of the subsequent fascicles must depend on the support, which the Department obtains, and on the space available, the laboratory being no longer accessible to me for even these purposes.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As several amateur collectors have aided in the issue, I would respectfully suggest that a copy be presented to D. Sullivan Esq of Moiston,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Moyston, Vic?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mr C. Walter of Anderson's Creek,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Rev Dr Woolls, FLS., Richmond, N. S. W., and Mr C. Groener.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
